## HARD STOP RULES (VIOLATION = IMMEDIATE REJECTION + ROLLBACK)
1. AccountingEntry MUST be 100% immutable (append-only). NEVER update or delete an existing entry.
2. Any financial change MUST create a new Reversal Entry (using ReversalEntryId).
3. Every entity MUST implement IMustHaveTenant with proper TenantId.
4. Domain layer MUST be pure: NO EF Core, NO DbContext, NO DataAnnotations, NO database logic.
5. Value Objects and Base Entities MUST exist ONLY in 1_Shared/Domain.cs (Source of Truth).
6. NO BYPASS ALLOWED: No stub files, no commenting out DbSets, no manual Version= in .csproj, no #pragma disable, no <GenerateAssemblyInfo>false, no SuppressMessage.
7. NAMESPACE INTEGRITY: VanAn.Shared.Domain is the single source of truth. Use clear aliases when needed. No duplicate entities across projects.
8. PLAN COMPLIANCE: Must strictly follow the approved Detailed Coding Plan. Any deviation must be explicitly marked "DEVIATION FROM APPROVED PLAN" and wait for Grok approval.

## MODULAR MONOLITH RULES (MANDATORY)
- All Business Logic MUST stay in CoreHub Services (VanAn.Accounting, VanAn.CoreHub.Services...).
- Controllers / Gateway / Hubs ONLY handle routing, validation, and orchestration.
- Database access MUST go through Repository Interfaces only.
- No business logic in Controllers, Gateway, or UI layers.

## DOMAIN & ARCHITECTURE RULES
- All Accounting logic must follow immutable append-only pattern with AccountingEntryFactory.
- Must support 4 HKD Books: RevenueBook, ExpenseBook, CashBankBook, TaxDeclarationBook.
- Multi-tenancy MUST be enforced at every layer (global query filters + explicit checks).
- Central Package Management (CPM) is mandatory. No manual Version= in any .csproj.

## IMPLEMENTATION WORKFLOW v6.0 (7 Mandatory Steps)
1. Use Case & Business Design (Grok + User)
2. Reverse Impact Analysis + TDD Plan (Windsurf)
3. Detailed Coding Plan + Namespace Strategy (Windsurf) <- MUST include full using/alias plan
4. Grok + User Review & Approve
5. Pre-Implementation Namespace Validation (paste 1 sample file + successful build)
6. Implementation by Phase
7. Review & Approval after each Phase (code + guard-check.ps1 + dotnet build VanAn.sln)

After each major phase:
- Paste changed/created files
- Run `.\guard-check.ps1` and `dotnet build VanAn.sln` 
- Wait for Grok explicit approval before continuing

## TDD ENFORCEMENT (MANDATORY)
- Write Unit Test + Integration Test BEFORE implementing any new business logic.
- Minimum 1 Unit Test + 1 Integration Test per important public method.
- All tests MUST pass before considering a part complete.

## ACCOUNTING CORE RULES (HIGHEST PRIORITY)
- All financial operations are append-only.
- Every AccountingEntry must have BookType, Period, Amount, Description, TenantId, CreatedAt, and optional ReversalEntryId.
- Use AccountingEntryFactory for all entry creation.
- Support both Hô Kinh Doanh (cash-basis) and basic Company accounting.

## GUARD & ANTI-HACK RULES (ZERO TOLERANCE)
1. Guard MUST return PASSED before any submission is accepted.
2. Always report the REAL guard and build result first.
3. Build target: `dotnet build VanAn.sln` 
4. No hacks to silence errors. Fix root cause only.

## FORBIDDEN (ZERO TOLERANCE)
- Duplicate domain entities
- EF Core / DbContext in Domain layer
- Update/Delete on AccountingEntry
- Silent catch blocks or empty try-catch
- Hardcoded/fake data in accounting flows
- Business logic in Controllers/Gateway/Hubs

Speed is important, but Accounting correctness, data integrity, immutability, multi-tenancy, and architectural cleanliness are NON-NEGOTIABLE.
